						<summary>

						<p>The chief receives among others the titles <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvaraṉ, Maṇḍalika-Dēvēndraṉ Saptāṅga Gaṅgan</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Saṅgrāmadhīraṉ.</hi> The inscription stops with the mention of the Śaka year. Some piece is evidently missing as in the <hi rend="italic">Report.</hi> It records the gift of an ornament by Śrīpatināyaṉ, son of the king (Śelva-Gaṅga).</p>						

						</summary>
